-- European Union's Carbon Emissions Allowances Advance 0.4% to 15.68 Euros
-- Ewa Krukowska
-- 2010-06-14T06:04:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/european-union-s-carbon-emissions-allowances-advance-0-4-to-15-68-euros.html

          
          
             Carbon permits under the European
Union’s emissions-trading system, the world’s biggest
cap-and-trade program, rose 0.4 percent.  
 EU allowances for December 2010 delivery traded at 15.68
euros a metric ton as of 7:04 a.m. on London’s European Climate
Exchange, compared with 15.62 euros at the close of the previous
session.   
